annotationA: Glucosylceramide synthase (GlcT-1) catalyzes the formation of glucosylceramide, the core component of glycosphingolipids. GlcT-1 regulates lipid energy metabolism in fat body and plays critical roles in embryo survival and development
annotationB: Ceramide kinase (Cerk) catalyzes phosphorylation of ceramide, helping to maintain ceramide levels, which in turn regulates photoreceptor structure and function. Cerk is also a component of WntD signaling and mediates primordial germ cell migration
